	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Some faction info for those who are curious.  The following text is taken directly from one of my log files.<BR>
<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] Oracle of K`Arnon is bathed in starfire.<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] You have slain Oracle of K`Arnon!<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] Your faction standing with OracleOfKarnon got worse.<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] Your faction standing with OracleOfMarud got better.<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] You gain experience!!<BR>
[Fri May 04 01:27:25 2001] Oracle of K`Ar says 'The death of a Dark Bargainer never goes unnoticed! <BR>
<BR>
Note several things.<BR>
<BR>
1. The positive faction adjustment is to the &quot;OracleOfMarud&quot; faction, not the &quot;OracleOfMaud&quot; faction.<BR>
2. This seems to be of little, if any, consequence for the simple reason that nobody seems to have the slightest clue about who, exactly, is the Oracle Of Marud.  [Or maybe, to be consistent, it might be the Oracle Of M'arud?]<BR>
3. Based on his spell casting it would be fair to assume that the Oracle is a Wizard.  I think everybody involved seems to agree that the Guardian is a Paladin.  Neither class has an innate ability to change their racial appearance.<BR>
4. Dark Bargainers is the name of the Dark Elf merchant's guild based in Neriak.  Both the Oracle and his Paladin guardian appear to be High Elves.  [Can you possibly imagine a less likely alliance than that?]<BR>
<BR>
My conclusion: There is more to this fellow and his affiliations than meets the eye.<BR>
<BR>
Some more observations:<BR>
<BR>
1. The Oracle does, indeed, still drop the robe.  I killed him at least a dozen times this spring (2001) and he never failed to drop the robe.<BR>
2. The Guardian can be harmonied by a druid to prevent him from trying to protect the Oracle.  Just harmony him, then pull the Oracle beyond the Guardian's agro range and you can kill the Oracle without worrying about the Guardian at all.<BR>
3. The Guardian is clearly not the place holder for the Oracle as the Oracle is often seen standing next to the Guardian.<BR>
4. The Oracle is on a timed spawn of about 6 hours.  I confirmed this many times by actually timing it while hunting at the Ancient Cyclops Camp which is within Tracking range for my Druid.<BR>
5. To cut down on the amount of damage you receive from the Oracle's spells, you need to pump up your resists versus magic, fire and cold.<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
