	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay, I'm back, I was the druid that tried to solo this guy at 43.<BR>
<BR>
I went in at 44 and of course he wasn't there, just my luck.  It took 3 real-life days to find him there.  I just bound at the docks and gated there from time to time.  If you run tracking you'll be able to tell if he's there without running to the island every time.<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, finally he's there.  I harmonize the guard and snare the oracle, then run along the coastline out of spell range.  He runs after me, and I'm clicking on the root spell like a wierdo on steroids until he gets into range.  Root takes and I give him the DOT, then run out of range.<BR>
<BR>
As the root broke, I just re-rooted and ran out of spell range.  When the dots broke I came back and re-dotted.<BR>
<BR>
2 dots and he was fleeing when root broke (level 44 dot is nice!).  I rooted him again then dotted one last time, then I noticed that I rooted him while was inside a tree!!<BR>
<BR>
After a few agonizing seconds he died and his corpse was visible to me.  Whew!  Got me a robe!<BR>
<BR>
I lost some faction, but only with him and his guardian buddy.  It doesn't lower high elf faction.  <BR>
<BR>
Happy hunting!<BR>
-Tenjo, level 44 druid of Bertox.-
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
