	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Okay, I was frustrated after reading post after post on this guy and not really any info whatsoever on soloing this guy.<BR>
<BR>
Here's what I&quot;ve found out:<BR>
(I'm a 43 wood-elf druid at this point)<BR>
<BR>
First, his guard can be harmonied no problem.  <BR>
<BR>
Second, there didn't seem to be anything on this island that would aggro me, INCLUDING the oracle or his bud.  I didn't hail him, but I walked right up to him no problem, and he conned indifferent to me.<BR>
<BR>
Third, he's level 35.  And EXACTLY 35.  He conned white last time I came to him, I was level 35.<BR>
<BR>
I tried to kill him twice, both times I had to gate with 1 bubble of health left.<BR>
<BR>
Tactic 1: Snare and kite<BR>
This doesn't work well against wizzies, but I figured the 8-level differnence and resistance to magic would help.  I snared him across the water and he started to cast.  He walked into the water, still casting on me.  Bummer because I couldn't cast on him.<BR>
<BR>
His tactic is some magic blast, then a frost blast, then he chain casts fire spells on you, something which druids have no resistance spells for.  It's the chain casting that buried me.  And, his spell range is larger than mine.  I ran over the water so his swimming would be slowed and gated.<BR>
<BR>
Attempt 2: Snare, root and dot.<BR>
I wanted to snare him first to get him away from the guard in case harmony wore off.  I snared him easily enough, but by the time I could root and get my first blast off, he had me under half health from those chain-casting fire spells, which did a bubble of damage each cast.<BR>
<BR>
I gave up in frustration, but I'm almost level 44 now.  I'll try my improved regen (chloroplast), magic resistance, and try to get a fire resist cast on me in the zone.  If I could have resisted just 1 or 2 of those blasts I'm sure he would be dead and I'd be talking about how easy he was to kill.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this is useful,<BR>
Tenjo, 43rd Druid on Bertoxx.<BR>
<BR>
Oh, and if you want to flame me on how easily you killed him at level 25, forget it.  Don't waste your fingers, I'm just reflecting the experience I had.  I've killed some mighty tough mobs by myself, and lost some fights that should have been really cake.  That's the way the dice roll in this game.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
